{"title": "Tech companies to meet on legal challenge to Trump immigration order", "text": "A group of technology companies is planning to meet on Tuesday to discuss filing an amicus brief in support of a lawsuit challenging U.S. President Donald Trump's order restricting immigration from seven Muslim-majority countries, said a spokesperson for GitHub, a company that makes software development tools, which is organizing the meeting.\n\nAlphabet Inc's Google, Airbnb Inc and Netflix Inc are among the companies invited to the meeting, a separate person familiar with the situation said.\n\n(Reporting by Dan Levine, Stephen Nellis, Kristina Cooke and Jeffrey Dastin; Editing by Bill Rigby)", "keywords": ["seven", "trump", "spokesperson", "technology", "challenge", "support", "companies", "immigration", "legal", "tech", "trumps", "situation", "stephen", "meet", "tools", "order", "software"], "epoch": "1485850378", "authors": ["Reuters Editorial"], "date": "20170131"}